"/\", routes![index])\n}\n```\n\n### Log Output\n\n```shell\n> # asking to run on a unix socket through an environment variable for brevity\n> ROCKET_LOG_LEVEL=debug ROCKET_ADDRESS=\"unix:/tmp/rocket_reuse.sock\" cargo run\n\n    Finished `dev` profile [unoptimized + debuginfo] target(s) in 0.22s\n     Running `target/debug/aaa`\n🔧 config (profile: debug)\n   >> http2: true\n   >> log_level: DEBUG\n   >> log_format: Pretty\n   >> cli_colors: auto\n   >> workers: 8\n   >> max_blocking: 512\n   >> ident: Rocket\n   >> ip_header: X-Real-IP\n   >> limits: {\"bytes\": 8KiB, \"data-form\": 2MiB, \"file\": 1MiB, \"form\": 32KiB, \"json\": 1MiB, \"msgpack\": 1MiB, \"string\": 8KiB}\n   >> temp_dir: /private/tmp/nix-shell-45129-168065028\n   >> keep_alive: 5\n   >> shutdown.ctrlc: true\n   >> shutdown.signals: {\"SIGTERM\"}\n   >> shutdown.grace: 2\n   >> shutdown.mercy: 3\n   >> shutdown.force: true\n   >> [DEBUG rocket::figment] param: workers source.name: rocket::Config::default() value: Num(U64(8))\n   >> [DEBUG rocket::figment] param: max_blocking source.name: rocket::Config::default() value: Num(U64(512))\n   >> [DEBUG rocket::figment] param: keep_alive source.name: rocket::Config::default() value: Num(U32(5))\n   >> [DEBUG rocket::figment] param: ident source.name: rocket::Config::default() value: String(\"Rocket\")\n   >> [DEBUG rocket::figment] param: ip_header source.name: rocket::Config::default() value: String(\"X-Real-IP\")\n   >> [DEBUG rocket::figment] param: proxy_proto_header source.name: rocket::Config::default() value: Empty(None)\n   >> [DEBUG rocket::figment] param: limits source.name: rocket::Config::default() value: Dict({\"bytes\": Num(U64(8192)), \"data-form\": Num(U64(2097152)), \"file\": Num(U64(1048576)), \"form\": Num(U64(32768)), \"json\": Num(U64(1048576)), \"msgpack\": Num(U64(1048576)), \"string\": Num(U64(8192))})\n   >> [DEBUG rocket::figment] param: temp_dir source.name: rocket::Config::default() value: String(\"/private/tmp/nix-shell-45129-168065028\")\n   >> [DEBUG rocket::figment] param: log_level source.name: `ROCKET_` environment variable(s) value: String(\"debug\")\n   >> [DEBUG rocket::figment] param: log_format source.name: rocket::Config::default() value: String(\"pretty\")\n   >> [DEBUG rocket::figment] param: shutdown source.name: rocket::Config::default() value: Dict({\"ctrlc\": Bool(true), \"force\": Bool(true), \"grace\": Num(U32(2)), \"mercy\": Num(U32(3)), \"signals\": Array([String(\"term\")])})\n   >> [DEBUG rocket::figment] param: cli_colors source.name: rocket::Config::default() value: String(\"Auto\")\n📬 routes (count: 1)\n   >> route:  -9 GET / (index src/main.rs:3)\n   >> [DEBUG rocket::sentinels] route: index sentinels: {}\n📦 fairings (count: 1)\n   >> fairing: Shield liftoff, response, singleton\nerror: launch failure aborting launch due to error\n   >> error: 🔧 config ()\n      :: error: missing field\n      ++ value: reuse\n```\n\n### Additional Context\n\nA workaround is to explicitly set the `reuse` value, with either `ROCKET_REUSE=true` or in `Rocket.toml`:\n\n```toml\n[default]\nreuse = true\n```\n\n\nWhen digging a bit in the source code, it seems this line is the problem: https://github.com/rwf2/Rocket/blob/504efef179622df82ba1dbd37f2e0d9ed2b7c9e4/core/lib/src/listener/unix.rs#L82\n\n\nNot a big deal, just wanted to point that out!\n\n### System Checks\n\n- [x] My bug report relates to functionality.\n- [x] I have tested against the latest Rocket release or a recent git commit.\n- [x] I have tested against the latest stable `rustc` toolchain.\n- [x] I was unable to find this issue previously reported.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2976/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2976/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2209","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2209/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2209/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2209/events","html_url":"https://github.com/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2209","id":1251898240,"node_id":"I_kwDOAzqMt85KnnOA","number":2209,"title":"Add support for diesel 2.0.0","user":{"login":"IonutCicio","id":40034429,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQwMDM0NDI5","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/40034429?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/IonutCicio","html_url":"https://github.com/IonutCicio","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/IonutCicio/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/IonutCicio/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/IonutCicio/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/IonutCicio/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/IonutCicio/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/IonutCicio/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/IonutCicio/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/IonutCicio/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/IonutCicio/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":758540633,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWw3NTg1NDA2MzM=","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/labels/suggestion","name":"suggestion","color":"5319E7","default":false,"description":"A suggestion to change functionality"}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":4,"created_at":"2022-05-29T14:03:11Z","updated_at":"2026-02-18T15:33:30Z","closed_at":"2022-09-18T08:47:06Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"NONE","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"**Existing Functionality**\r\n\r\n`rocket_sync_db_pools` currently relies on `diesel 1.4`, which is going [out of support](https://github.com/diesel-rs/diesel/issues/2348#issuecomment-1140445903), and it's currently giving some problems with `uuid 1.0.0`.\r\n\r\n- `diesel 1.4` supports up to `uuid 0.8` and rocket `0.5.0-rc` has functionalities for `uuid 1.0`, creating a conflict: if I want to use `uuid::Uuid` in the models, I must use version 0.8, but, if I want a uuid in a route, I must use `rocket::serde::uuid::Uuid`, which isn't compatible with the diesel implementation. To handle this problem, I downgraded the uuid version to 0.8, and created a conversion function:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\npub fn to_uuid(id: rocket::serde::uuid::Uuid) -> Result<uuid::Uuid, uuid::Error> {\r\n    Uuid::parse_str(id.to_string().as_str())\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhich means I must manually use it everytime I want to use a Uuid in a request_:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\n#[get(\"/<id>\")]\r\npub async fn get_id(id: rocket::serde::uuid::Uuid, db: Db) -> Json<User> {\r\n    let id = to_uuid(id).unwrap();\r\n    \r\n    ...\r\n}\r\n```\r\n- It also means that I have to handle 2 Uuids in my code, which can be confusing in some parts.\r\n- The other problem is that the `1.4.x` won't be supported anymore, so it would be really useful to transition to `2.0.0` as soon as it's ready.\r\n- The current version is missing some of the [new functionalities](https://github.com/diesel-rs/diesel/releases/tag/v2.0.0-rc0) like group by, table aliasing, \"Selectable\" trait, union, intersect and except.\r\n\r\nA clear and concise description of existing functionality and why it is insufficient. Examples:\r\n\r\n**Suggested Changes**\r\n\r\nI still haven't looked at the code to find a solution, and it would still be too soon to upgrade to the new version, as it's not fully ready yet.\r\n\r\n**Alternatives Considered**\r\n\r\nI've tried to implement the `Poolable` trait for `diesel 2.0.0`'s `PgConnection` inside my project, but it's really complex, as I can't directly implement the trait to `diesel::PgConnection` due to the [orphan rule](https://doc.rust-lang.org/book/ch19-03-advanced-traits.html?highlight=orphan#using-the-newtype-pattern-to-implement-external-traits-on-external-types).\r\n\r\n I can implement `Poolable` only if I wrap diesel::PgConnection with a custom struct\r\n```rust\r\npub struct Connection(diesel::PgConnection); \r\n```\r\n\r\nBut I manually have to implement a custom manager, and all the other traits `diesel:PgConnection` uses.\r\n```rust\r\nimpl Poolable for Connection {\r\n    type Manager = ....;\r\n    ...\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Additional Context**\r\n\r\n`diesel 2.0.0` it's still not ready, I suggest waiting  before trying to implement anything. I would also be glad to hear some suggestions, or the problems this feature can create.\r\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2209/reactions","total_count":4,"+1":3,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":1,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2209/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rustls/rustls/issues/2577","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rustls/rustls","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rustls/rustls/issues/2577/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rustls/rustls/issues/2577/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rustls/rustls/issues/2577/events","html_url":"https://github.com/rustls/rustls/issues/2577","id":3265623437,"node_id":"I_kwDOA3PM4M7CpXWN","number":2577,"title":"Can't seem to load ML-DSA private key with rustls-post-quantum 0.2.3","user":{"login":"SebastienRaveau","id":25374616,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI1Mzc0NjE2","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/25374616?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/SebastienRaveau","html_url":"https://github.com/SebastienRaveau","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SebastienRaveau/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SebastienRaveau/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SebastienRaveau/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SebastienRaveau/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SebastienRaveau/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SebastienRaveau/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SebastienRaveau/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SebastienRaveau/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SebastienRaveau/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":8,"created_at":"2025-07-26T13:22:10Z","updated_at":"2025-09-23T15:25:09Z","closed_at":"2025-09-23T15:18:05Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"NONE","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"**Checklist**\n* [X] I've searched the issue tracker for similar bugs.\n\n**Describe the bug**\nHi! Many thanks for adding PQC DSA beyond the PQC KEM support that rustls-post-quantum already accomplished, both much appreciated and I understand that this new addition came clearly labeled \"add _unstable_ ML-DSA support\" but I can't seem to get it to load any ML-DSA private key despite trying:\n\n- mine generated with OpenSSL 3.5.1 (which has native ML-DSA support since 3.5.0)\n- mine generated on another computer with OpenSSL 3.4.1 and oqsprovider 0.9.0\n- the one corresponding to the test certificate linked [in the PR thread](https://github.com/rustls/webpki/pull/348#issuecomment-2984029964)\n\nThe error I am stuck at is \"failed to parse private key as RSA, ECDSA, or EdDSA\" which exists in 4 different places in rusts 0.23.29 source but I managed to track it down specifically to [aws_lc_rs/sign.rs#L36](https://github.com/rustls/rustls/blob/v/0.23.29/rustls/src/crypto/aws_lc_rs/sign.rs#L36) which is all about RSA, ECDSA and EdDSA indeed... If I understand its Cargo.toml correctly, rustls-post-quantum (with \"aws-lc-rs-unstable\" feature enabled) is not at all a fork of rustls (and \"aws-lc-rs\" feature) but the former actually depend on the latest stable release of the latter, however may I ask if it is normal that loading my PQC creds happens in the non-PQC part? 🙂 \n\nI mean, it is entirely possible that I misunderstood the \"Experimental support for ML-DSA signature schemes is now available via rustls-post-quantum 0.2.3\" announcement: perhaps for now the support is only for validating a certificate presented by a remote peer as opposed to loading your own ML-DSA files like I am trying to do?\n\n**To Reproduce**\nI guess the best way would be to try to add Mutual TLS support in the existing rustls-post-quantum/examples/client.rs or to implement a corresponding \"server.rs\" but what I have been trying so far is simply with rocket.rs (from main branch, not the latest 0.5.1 release which still tries to parse keys by itself even if the crypto provider is overridden) with the very first instruction being `rustls_post_quantum::provider().install_default().unwrap();` as per rustls documentation or `let _ = rustls_post_quantum::provider().install_default();` as inferred from rocket documentation.\n\nPS: if like me you/someone tries to patch rustls to help figure out what is going on in rustls-post-quantum, beware that unpatched rustls can still be brought in by rocket and tokio-rustls for example.\n\n**Applicable Version(s)**\nrustls-post-quantum 0.2.3\nrustls 0.23.29\nhttps://github.com/rwf2/Rocket/tree/master since May the 4th\n\n**Expected behavior**\nSame as always with TLS the only difference being credentials of the ML-DSA type instead of RSA, ECDSA or EdDSA. Further explained in the \"Load/validate and parse Quantum certificates generated by oqsprovider\" issue #2417 with now the addition of files generated by OpenSSL>=3.5.0 itself.\n\n**Additional context**\nHaving edited rustls-post-quantum/src/lib.rs I am quite confident that I successfully forced rocket to use rustls-post-quantum instead of any other crypto provider, but private key parsing still seems to go from rustls-post-quantum into non-PQC rustls code; maybe more ML-DSA patches are needed in rustls and/or rustls-pemfile?","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rustls/rustls/issues/2577/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rustls/rustls/issues/2577/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/edly-io/sparkth/issues/78","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/edly-io/sparkth","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/edly-io/sparkth/issues/78/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/edly-io/sparkth/issues/78/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/edly-io/sparkth/issues/78/events","html_url":"https://github.com/edly-io/sparkth/issues/78","id":3456931738,"node_id":"I_kwDOO8Z3-c7ODJea","number":78,"title":"Explore our options for backend/frontend infrastructure","user":{"login":"regisb","id":44319,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ0MzE5","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/44319?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/regisb","html_url":"https://github.com/regisb","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/regisb/followers","following_u