rkth will evolve from an MCP server to a full-fledged web app. For that, we need to decide which frontend and backend frameworks we will use. We need to conduct a review of our existing options. Similar to what we did for WebUIs: https://docs.edly.space/doc/llm-webuis-QVHlJB3ZOn","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/edly-io/sparkth/issues/78/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/edly-io/sparkth/issues/78/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2927","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2927/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2927/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2927/events","html_url":"https://github.com/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2927","id":2973772728,"node_id":"I_kwDOAzqMt86xQCu4","number":2927,"title":"Add support for the 'Origin-Agent-Cluster' header in rocket::shield","user":{"login":"AverageHelper","id":1500092,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE1MDAwOTI=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1500092?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/AverageHelper","html_url":"https://github.com/AverageHelper","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/AverageHelper/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/AverageHelper/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/AverageHelper/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/AverageHelper/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/AverageHelper/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/AverageHelper/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/AverageHelper/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/AverageHelper/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/AverageHelper/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":442152232,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWw0NDIxNTIyMzI=","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/labels/request","name":"request","color":"5319E7","default":false,"description":"Request for new functionality"}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":2,"created_at":"2025-04-05T02:41:07Z","updated_at":"2025-04-07T03:55:27Z","closed_at":"2025-04-05T09:55:20Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"NONE","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### What's missing?\n\nShield has structures for type-safe use of several standard security headers. Missing among those supported is [`Origin-Agent-Cluster`](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Reference/Headers/Origin-Agent-Cluster). An additional Shield Policy structure for this header would be very useful for those who wish to enable it.\n\n### Ideal Solution\n\nSince the header only has one permitted value (`?1`), a new `enum` would be very simple, and might be shaped very similarly to the existing `NoSniff` policy enum:\n\n```rust\npub enum OriginCluster {\n    Enable,\n}\n```\n\nThe default value would of course be the enum's sole member, `Enable`.\n\n### Why can't this be implemented outside of Rocket?\n\nThis header relates to specific security concerns, the sort of thing one might expect to find covered by Shield. Outside implementations are possible, but overkill IMO.\n\n### Are there workarounds usable today?\n\nUsers today may send this header themselves using a custom fairing, in addition to any existing Shield fairing they may have installed.\n\n### Alternative Solutions\n\nThe name of the structure itself and its value are arbitrary. In drafting my proposed one, `OriginCluster`, I tried to follow the examples of the other policy structures and capture the structure's purpose without being too wordy. But other different or more verbose spellings would work just as well.\n\n### Additional Context\n\nI attempted to implement this change myself, including relevant unit tests, at https://github.com/rwf2/Rocket/commit/e4c598f68d8837a2509bd94afe3e450420fdcfc6, if approved I will start a PR on this. I hope I'm following the contribution policy closely enough, this is my first one here 😅\n\n### System Checks\n\n- [x] I do not believe that this feature can or should be implemented outside of Rocket.\n- [x] I was unable to find a previous request for this feature.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2927/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2927/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/jebrosen/rocket_oauth2/issues/38","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/jebrosen/rocket_oauth2","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/jebrosen/rocket_oauth2/issues/38/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/jebrosen/rocket_oauth2/issues/38/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/jebrosen/rocket_oauth2/issues/38/events","html_url":"https://github.com/jebrosen/rocket_oauth2/issues/38","id":1433135993,"node_id":"I_kwDOCUdDYs5Va-t5","number":38,"title":"Cookie `rocket_oauth2_state` with `secure` flag","user":{"login":"atezet","id":4867268,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ4NjcyNjg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/4867268?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/atezet","html_url":"https://github.com/atezet","followers_url":"https://a