ore::varint::VarInt>`\r\n              `s2n_quic::application::Error` implements `From<u16>`\r\n              `s2n_quic::application::Error` implements `From<u32>`\r\n              `s2n_quic::application::Error` implements `From<u8>`\r\n    = note: required for `s2n_quic_core::varint::VarInt` to implement `Into<s2n_quic::application::Error>`\r\n\r\nFor more information about this error, try `rustc --explain E0277`.\r\nerror: could not compile `s2n-quic-h3` (lib) due to 2 previous errors\n```\n\n\n### Additional Context\n\nI believe one way to fix this, is to merge in upstream fix from https://github.com/aws/s2n-quic/issues/2313#issuecomment-2362059801 into https://github.com/SergioBenitez/s2n-quic-h3 and then update the revision in `core/lib/Cargo.toml`\r\n\r\nReferences:\r\n\r\n* https://github.com/rwf2/Rocket/issues/1067#issuecomment-2377308966 mentions this test problem\r\n* https://github.com/aws/s2n-quic/issues/2313\r\n* https://app.element.io/#/room/#rocket:mozilla.org/$7dIHXmw9p5EWnrkV6vBjqhQXeXrsUmx3HFHUQR0x66I\r\n    Sergio mentioned this problem Sep 2nd on the matrix chat\r\n\r\nFinal Notes:\r\n\r\n* This is my first issue for Rocket, so definitely point out any mistakes I've made\r\n* This was on FreeBSD, but I *believe* this problem would still exist on other OSs\n\n### System Checks\n\n- [X] My bug report relates to functionality.\n- [X] I have tested against the latest Rocket release or a recent git commit.\n- [X] I have tested against the latest stable `rustc` toolchain.\n- [X] I was unable to find this issue previously reported.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2877/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2877/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2270","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2270/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2270/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2270/events","html_url":"https://github.com/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2270","id":1306406731,"node_id":"I_kwDOAzqMt85N3i9L","number":2270,"title":"Adding support for modifying fairings","user":{"login":"the10thWiz","id":16281943,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE2MjgxOTQz","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/16281943?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/the10thWiz","html_url":"https://github.com/the10thWiz","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/the10thWiz/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/the10thWiz/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/the10thWiz/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/the10thWiz/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/the10thWiz/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/the10thWiz/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/the10thWiz/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/the10thWiz/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/the10thWiz/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":442152232,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWw0NDIxNTIyMzI=","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/labels/request","name":"request","color":"5319E7","default":false,"description":"Request for new functionality"}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":1,"created_at":"2022-07-15T19:26:15Z","updated_at":"2024-08-24T10:19:26Z","closed_at":"2024-08-24T10:19:25Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"I believe Rocket should provide support for modifying fairings during the ignite phase. This would enable, for example, an API for fairings to register template functions automatically. I'm working on a rocket-auth crate that provides convenient and secure authentication, and I would like the ability to register a template function that provides a pre-built login template, or the Sign in with Google button. This can't simply be a template macro, since at least the Google button requires some things like the API key in the HTML.\r\n\r\n**Why this feature can't or shouldn't live outside of Rocket**\r\n\r\nThere are two parts to the feature described above, and only the first needs to live in Rocket's core. To provide a simple and flexible system, Rocket should likely only provide a mutable reference to previously registered fairings. The ability to add functions to the template engine should be implemented in `rocket_dyn_templates`. In this way, Fairings can define in what ways they can be modified, preventing unexpected interactions.\r\n\r\n**Ideal Solution**\r\n\r\nI think the ideal solution should look something like this. Since every other method on `Rocket<Build>` takes `self`, I think it's appropriate for modify_fairing to as well. This should also be quite reasonable to call from within an ignite fairing, since the return type works for it.\r\n\r\n```rust\r\nimpl Rocket<Build> {\r\n    pub fn modify_fairing<F: Fairing, E: Error>(self, f: Fn(&mut F) -> Result<(), E>) -> Result<Self, Self>;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThere are a few issues to consider. First, Fairings are held as `Box<dyn Fairing>`, however this is actually pretty trivial since Fairings must implement Any. Second, it's possible there are multiple Fairings of a given type. In that case, I think it's best to simply run the function on each instance. If any instance fails (or there are none), modify_fairing should return Err.\r\n\r\n**Alternatives Considered**\r\n\r\nAt the moment, something like this is kind of possible (at least for template functions), but it requires some somewhat ugly code in the main function. Ideally, the somewhat ugly code should be in the library providing the template, if it cannot be eliminated entirely.\r\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2270/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2270/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2844","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2844/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2844/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2844/events","html_url":"https://github.com/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2844","id":2460258318,"node_id":"I_kwDOAzqMt86SpJAO","number":2844,"title":"Implement `PartialEq` for `http::Status` with derive macro","user":{"login":"frondeus","id":1165825,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjExNjU4MjU=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1165825?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/frondeus","html_url":"https://github.com/frondeus","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/frondeus/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/frondeus/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/frondeus/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/frondeus/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/frondeus/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/frondeus/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/frondeus/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/frondeus/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/frondeus/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":758540633,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWw3NTg1NDA2MzM=","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/labels/suggestion","name":"suggestion","color":"5319E7","default":false,"description":"A suggestion to change functionality"}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":4,"created_at":"2024-08-12T07:38:03Z","updated_at":"2024-08-19T22:52:46Z","closed_at":"2024-08-19T22:52:46Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"NONE","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### API Docs to Existing Functionality\n\nhttps://api.rocket.rs/v0.5/rocket/http/struct.Status\n\n### Problems with Existing Functionality\n\nStatus does not implement `PartialEq` via `derive(PartialEq)`, which causes it to lack `StructuralPartialEq`.\r\n\r\nIt prohibits using status in match:\r\n\r\n```rs\r\nmatch status {\r\n    Status::Unauthorized => { ... },\r\n    Status::NotFound => { ... },\r\n    _ => { ... }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nbecause `Status::Unauthorized` is a constant which triggers error:\r\n\r\n```\r\nerror: to use a constant of type `rocket::http::Status` in a pattern, `rocket::http::Status` must be annotated with `#[derive(PartialEq)]`\r\n  --> my_project/src/errors.rs:40:13\r\n   |\r\n40 |             Status::Unauthorized => { ... },\r\n   |             ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\r\n   |\r\n   = note: the traits must be derived, manual `impl`s are not sufficient\r\n   = note: see https://doc.rust-lang.org/stable/std/marker/trait.StructuralPartialEq.html for details\r\n``` \n\n### Suggested Changes\n\nI've looked at current implementation of `PartialEq` for `Status`:\r\nhttps://github.com/rwf2/Rocket/blob/1a3ef5b23fdf4a4619fa9b5d3f24cff6f8008085/core/http/src/status.rs#L363C1-L367C2\r\n\r\nAnd it seems that there is nothing prohibiting automatic derive. \n\n### Alternatives Considered\n\nAn alternative solution to my `match` expression is something like this:\r\n\r\n```rs\r\nmatch status {\r\n    status if status == Status::Unauthorized => { ... },\r\n    status if status == Status::TooManyRequests => { ... },\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut it doesn't feel idiomatic. \r\n\r\nAnother would be to use code directly:\r\n\r\n```rs\r\nmatch status.code {\r\n    401 => { ... },\r\n    429 => { ... }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut here I'm more prone to the typo than using existing constant.\n\n### Additional Context\n\n_No response_\n\n### System Checks\n\n- [X] I do not believe that this suggestion can or should be implemented outside of Rocket.\n\n- [X] I was unable to find a previous suggestion for this change.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2844/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2844/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/356","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/356/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/356/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/356/events","html_url":"https://github.com/rwf2/Rocket/issues/356","id":244231418,"node_id":"MDU6SXNzdWUyNDQyMzE0MTg=","number":356,"title":"generated param `match`es contain unignored unreachable patterns","user":{"login":"durka","id":47007,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3MDA3","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47007?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com