ikhuijzer/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":442152232,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWw0NDIxNTIyMzI=","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/labels/request","name":"request","color":"5319E7","default":false,"description":"Request for new functionality"},{"id":442158786,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWw0NDIxNTg3ODY=","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/labels/declined","name":"declined","color":"E99695","default":false,"description":"A declined request or suggestion"}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":3,"created_at":"2024-02-16T09:36:18Z","updated_at":"2024-08-24T10:18:37Z","closed_at":"2024-08-24T10:18:28Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"NONE","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### What's missing?\n\nFirst of all, thanks for making Rocket. I like it a lot.\r\n\r\nI would like to open a feature request. Whenever I change my templates or Rocket code, Rocket restarts automatically with\r\n```sh\r\ncargo watch -x run\r\n```\r\nas described in https://github.com/rwf2/Rocket/issues/292#issuecomment-730392516. However, my browser doesn't automatically refresh the page meaning that I manually have to refresh it upon each change.\n\n### Ideal Solution\n\nThe ideal solution would be something like what is used in the `npm` `live-server` package. There, some Javascript is injected which connects to an open socket. Whenever the server reloads some files, the browser receives a notification and reloads the page.\n\n### Why can't this be implemented outside of Rocket?\n\nI wouldn't know how to implement this outside of Rocket. \n\n### Are there workarounds usable today?\n\nYes. One workaround that works reasonably well for me is to inject the following Javascript into my HTML pages when in development mode:\r\n```javascript\r\n<script>\r\n  function check_reload() {\r\n      fetch(\"/check_reload\").then(response => response.text()).then(data => {\r\n          if (data === \"true\") {\r\n              location.reload();\r\n          }\r\n      });\r\n  }\r\n  setInterval(check_reload, 2000);\r\n</script>\r\n```\r\nand to add the following endpoint to my Rocket server:\r\n```rust\r\nlazy_static! {\r\n    static ref SHOULD_RELOAD: Mutex<bool> = Mutex::new(true);\r\n}\r\n\r\n#[get(\"/check_reload\")]\r\nasync fn check_reload() -> String {\r\n    let mut should_reload = SHOULD_RELOAD.lock().unwrap();\r\n    if *should_reload {\r\n        *should_reload = false;\r\n        return \"true\".to_string();\r\n    } else {\r\n        return \"false\".to_string();\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\nSo, what happens here is that the browser asks Rocket ever 2 seconds whether the browser should reload. If Rocket just reloaded, the answer is `true`. If Rocket has been asked this before but didn't restart, then the answer is `false`.\r\n\r\nThere are some drawbacks to this approach though:\r\n1. I have to set `log_level = \"critical\"` in `Rocket.toml` to avoid seeing one request pop up every 2 seconds (this would not happen with a socket).\r\n1. The browser \"network\" inspection tools are full of requests (this would not happen with a socket).\r\n1. There is a delay of 2 seconds before the page reloads (or even more requests spamming the logs).\r\n1. I'm not using templates currently, but I think my logic will not work correctly there.\r\n\n\n### Alternative Solutions\n\nIdeally, something would wrap around Rocket which keeps track of changes and keeps a socket open. Whenever Rocket then changes, it would notify the browser. I guess this could be something like nginx but then with some logic to track whether Rocket changed.\n\n### Additional Context\n\n_No response_\n\n### System Checks\n\n- [X] I do not believe that this feature can or should be implemented outside of Rocket.\n- [X] I was unable to find a previous request for this feature.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2728/reactions","total_count":4,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":4,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2728/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"not_planned","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2718","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2718/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2718/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2718/events","html_url":"https://github.com/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2718","id":2110748590,"node_id":"I_kwDOAzqMt859z3eu","number":2718,"title":"FileServer can serve pre-gzipped content if it exists on the filesystem","user":{"login":"hcldan","id":648319,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjY0ODMxOQ==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/648319?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/hcldan","html_url":"https://github.com/hcldan","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hcldan/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hcldan/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hcldan/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hcldan/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hcldan/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hcldan/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hcldan/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hcldan/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hcldan/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":442152232,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWw0NDIxNTIyMzI=","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/labels/request","name":"request","color":"5319E7","default":false,"description":"Request for new functionality"}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":4,"created_at":"2024-01-31T18:47:40Z","updated_at":"2024-08-22T11:26:26Z","closed_at":"2024-08-22T11:26:26Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### What's missing?\n\nRather than having to gzip on the fly, [other static file server middleware](https://www.npmjs.com/package/express-static-gzip) have the ability to serve a pre-gzipped file based on the file name and extension to avoid the overhead of gzip on the fly (sometimes this feature can even create the gzipped file the first time so subsequent requests can make use of it).\n\n### Ideal Solution\n\nAt the very minimum, check if there is a .gz file for the resource in question. If there is, use that file content instead, set the appropriate content-encoding, and use the non-gz extension for the content-type.\n\n### Why can't this be implemented outside of Rocket?\n\nI tried wrapping the FileServer but I couldn't edit the request to change the URI...  and even if I could, I'm not sure that's a really clean way of doing things... because the request wasn't *for* that file.\n\n### Are there workarounds usable today?\n\nNothing that I've found that is maintainable.\n\n### Alternative Solutions\n\nMaybe if fileServer could be given an optional function to help locating the source of the file and adjusting the header.\r\n\r\nThat could still lead to confusion when trying to set the correct headers based on a previous call to another function that redirected the source of the response.  Would make the attempt to unify the response very disjointed.\n\n### Additional Context\n\nFileServer lacks gzip capabilities, and issues in the past on this tracker have lamented the performance of gip-on-the-fly approaches.\n\n### System Checks\n\n- [X] I do not believe that this feature can or should be implemented outside of Rocket.\n- [X] I was unable to find a previous request for this feature.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2718/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":1,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/2718/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/stefano-garzarella/snp-svsm-vtpm/issues/7","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/stefano-garzarella/snp-svsm-vtpm","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/stefano-garzarella/snp-svsm-vtpm/issues/7/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/stefano-garzarella/snp-svsm-vtpm/issues/7/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/stefano-garzarella/snp-svsm-vtpm/issues/7/events","html_url":"https://github.com/stefano-garzarella/snp-svsm-vtpm/issues/7","id":2619927105,"node_id":"I_kwDOMErWBM6cKOpB","number":7,"title":"Database pool init error","user":{"login":"JinLiul","id":107175019,"node_id":"U_kgDOBmNcaw","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/107175019?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/JinLiul","html_url":"https://github.com/JinLiul","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JinLiul/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JinLiul/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JinLiul/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JinLiul/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JinLiul/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JinLiul/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JinLi